  "time_ut": 1662359520,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4\u0da2\u0db1 \u0db4\u0dd9\u0dad\u0dca\u0dc3\u0db8\u0dca  \u0dc3\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0dc3\u0db7\u0dcf\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0dad\u0db1\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dca \u0da2\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc2\u0dca\u0db4\u0d9a\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Jagath Pushpakumara is once again the chairman of the People's Petition Council",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member of Parliament Mr. Jagath Pushpakumara was re-elected as the Chairman of the Committee on Public Petitions in the third session of the Ninth Parliament.",
        "The first meeting of the Committee on Public Petitions was held on the 1st and this appointment was made in that meeting.",
        "Mr. Jagath Pushpakumara's name for the post of Chairman was proposed by Member of Parliament Mr. Priyankara Jayaratne and it was seconded by Member of Parliament Vadivel Suresh.",
        "Mr. Jagath Pushpakumara was also the chairman of the Committee on Public Petitions in the second term of the Ninth Parliament.",
        "Members of the Committee on Public Petitions were recently appointed by the Select Committee of Parliament in terms of Standing Order 120 (1).",
        "Accordingly, Gamini Valeboda, Imtiaz Bakir Makar, Pyankara Jayaratne, Dilip Vedaarachchi, Vadivel Suresh, S. Vyalendran, Ashoka Priyantha, Arvind Kumar, Geetha Samanmalee Kumarasinghe, B. Y. G. Ratnasekara, Sarathy Dushmantha, Govindan Karunakaram, Jayantha Katagoda, Mohammad Mussammil, Thushara Indunil Amarasena, Velu Kumar, Varuna Liyanage, U. K. Sumit Udukumbura, Mayadunna Chinthaka Amal, Nipuna Ranawaka and Rajika Wickramasinghe."
      ],
